HEADWORD: Tripartition
<hw>Trip`ar*ti"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tripartition</ets>.]</ety> <def>A division by threes, or into three
parts; the taking of a third part of any number or quantity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

